frameDefinitions: The words in this frame describe situations in which an Agent or a Cause injures a Victim.
An Experiencer is in a State where a biological urge is signaling the need to perform a certain action such as eating, drinking, stopping exertion, sleeping, regurgitating, or having sex.
An Executioner punishes an individual (Executed) with death as a consequence of some action of the Evaluee (the Reason).
An Agent causes the ballistic motion of a projectile and its subsequent impact on a Target.
A Combatant is declared or loyal to a Side in a military Conflict.
A Protagonist has (or does not have) a Weapon.
frameExamples: Rod saw his father <t>beating</t> his mother.
It looks like he <t>hit</t> the bull's-eye with his first arrow!
A 20-year=old Argentinian <t>guerilla</t> was firing at our squad.
Apparently, the suspect is <t>armed</t> with a shotgun.
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Agent</fen> is the person causing the <fen>Victim</fen>'s injury.

The <fen>Victim</fen> is the being or entity that is injured.  If the <fen>Victim</fen> is included in the phrase indicating <fen>Body_part</fen>, the <fen>Victim</fen> role is tagged on a second role layer (see 3rd example).
The <fen>Body_part</fen> identifies the location on the body where the bodily injury takes place.
The <fen>Cause</fen> marks expressions that indicate some non-intentional, typically non-human, force that inflicts harm on the <fen>Victim</fen>
<fen>Time</fen> identifies the time when the harm-causing event occurs.
<fen>Place</fen> identifies the place where the harm causing event occurs.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> receives the biological signal and possesses the internal experience which is a reaction to the phsyical signal.
<fen>Expressor</fen> is used for a gesture, expression, or body part indicating that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is feeling a certain urge.
<fen>State</fen> identifies the <fen>Experiencer</fen>'s state of being.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> feels the biological signal. <fen>Time</fen> may also allow inference about the <fen>Reason</fen> for the biological urge.
This role identifies the  <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Experiencer</fen> feels the biological signal.
The <fen>Executioner</fen> is the individual who performs the execution.
The <fen>Executed</fen> is the person who is killed by the <fen>Executioner</fen> in retribution for the crime that the <fen>Executed</fen> was convicted of.
When the execution occurs.
Where the execution takes place.
The entity which is hit by a Projectile directed by the Agent.
The individual that directs the Projectile such that it impacts the Target.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> hits the <fen>Target</fen>.
The location where the event happens.
The <fen>Combatant</fen> is the human being involved in combat.
The destructive device that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has with them.
The individual that possesses a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The location where a <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
